Transmission Electron Microscope (TEM) graphic of DT-CDs reveal uniform spherical morphology and well dispersed, and has an average diameter of 5–7 nm (Fig. 1
                        ). It was displayed that the modification of CDs with diarylethene did not affect its morphology and did not cause them to aggregate. The XRD pattern of DT-CDs (Fig. 2
                        ) exhibited a broad diffraction peak centered at 20.5°, corresponding to the C (002) plane of amorphous carbon, which was consistent with the high-resolution TEM image of CDs (Fig. S3). The result indicated that the graphene structure was reserved in the covalent linkage process of the CDs with diarylethene.
